How to install GOLANG :

########################

	- Download "golang" package : 
"wget -c https://storage.googleapis.com/golang/go1.7.3.linux-amd64.tar.gz"
##Check for last version on golang.org

	- Extract :
"sudo tar -C /usr/local -xvzf go1.7.3.linux-amd64.tar.gz"

	- Configure your environment :
"mkdir -p ../DevFolder/go_projects/{bin,src,pkg}" => cd ../DevFolder/go_projects

	- Add to PATH in your /etc/profile:
"export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/go/bin"

	- Add environment variables in your bash_profile
export GOPATH="../DevFolder/go_projects"
export GOBIN="$GOPATH/bin"

	-Reboot or reload your bash_profile

	- Check your installation :
"go version"
"go env"

###################################################################

How to import server :

########################

	- Pull the last version of the project on :
"https://github.com/abdoulillo/ISIBOpen-source"

	- Copy content of ISIB_SERVER folder into your go_projects/src folder

	- Go into your src folder and run the server :
"go run isib_server.go"

